{
  "uuid": "9d55aa4dd6747c1931ccfa1f5945d0cb",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Quantity Surveyor Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview</strong></p><p>ID INTEGRATED PTE. LTD. Interior Design and Build Company</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Support the Quantity Surveying function by preparing accurate cost estimates, tender documents, and progress claims, while managing procurement and supplier negotiations to ensure successful delivery of interior design and fit-out projects.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Support the Head of Quantity Surveying by managing key deliverables and contributing to project cost control</li><li>Prepare detailed quotations, cost estimates, and bills of quantities to inform project budgeting and tender submissions</li><li>Develop tender and contract documents, including quantity take-offs, material sourcing, and cost estimation to facilitate competitive bidding</li><li>Source and procure materials by negotiating effectively with suppliers and subcontractors to optimize project costs</li><li>Evaluate price comparisons and prepare comprehensive costing summaries to support decision-making</li><li>Prepare and submit monthly progress claims to clients, ensuring accurate and timely invoicing</li><li>Verify and maintain records of project variation works and site instructions to manage scope changes and costs</li><li>Attend site surveys as required to gather data for accurate quantity surveying and project assessment</li><li>Perform other quantity surveying duties as assigned to support project delivery and team objectives</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or Bachelor's Degree in Quantity Surveying</li><li>Minimum 2 years of experience in a Design & Build or similar environment, preferably specializing in fit-out or interior design projects</li><li>Experience managing large commercial or corporate office fit-out projects, including new builds and renovations</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Office applications including Excel, Word, and PowerPoint</li><li>Familiarity with MEP systems and Brava software is advantageous</li><li>Knowledge of the Gebiz tender process is beneficial</li><li>Ability to multi-task, prioritize, and organize tasks effectively to meet project deadlines</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 2,
